description.narrative: Vulnerable girls and boys, adolescents and youth have increased access to inclusive and quality formal and non-formal education., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Learning Outcomes, Prevention And Response Services For Violence Against Children, Sanitation, Skills Development, Water. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2020 children, adolescents, youth and their families, especially the most disadvantaged, are increasingly using improved quality basic services.

description.narrative: In the first half of 2020, 7,703 children/adolescents studied primary or lower secondary education through alternative modes of delivery (formal or non-formal, e.g. evening school, weekend school, distance learning) with support of UNICEF.
